body.description: Audio Fanatics Upgrade their Factory Sound with Rockford Fosgate! P16 The P16 is a pair of 6” 2-way full-range speakers rated at 55 watts RMS and designed for audio fanatics needing a quality factory replacement. The P16 offers a Flex Fit basket to ensure compatibility with odd shaped factory speaker locations and an ICC (Integrated Concealed Crossover), eliminating the need to mount any black boxes. The PEI dome tweeter provides accurate frequency reproduction as well as high volume output. The P16 is exactly what you need to replace your OEM factory speakers with, impressive sounding speakers built with high quality materials in an easy to install package.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Audio Fanatics Upgrade their Factory Sound with Rockford Fosgate! P16 The P16 is a pair of 6” 2-way full-range speakers rated at 55 watts RMS and designed for audio fanatics needing a quality factory replacement. The P16 offers a Flex Fit basket to ensure compatibility with odd shaped factory speaker locations and an ICC (Integrated Concealed Crossover), eliminating the need to mount any black boxes. The PEI dome tweeter provides accurate frequency reproduction as well as high volume output. The P16 is exactly what you need to replace your OEM factory speakers with, impressive sounding speakers built with high quality materials in an easy to install package. Speaker Size: 6 Inch Impedance: 4-Ohm Power Handling: 55 Watts RMS / 110 Watts Peak Frequency Response: 65Hz - 22kHz Mounting Depth: 1.93"

Flex Fit Basket Design The slot mounted frame pattern of the Flex Fit basket utilizes slots instead of single screw sized holes. This allows for a slight adjustment of the speaker when mounted for a better fit. Injection Molded Cone Our high strength injection molded polypropylene cone is rigid and lightweight to minimize any cone flex during use, improving the speakers overall sound quality while reducing potential distortion Integrated Crossover The Integrated Concealed Crossover hides the crosssover inside the basket, creating a cleaner look and easier installation. It also ensures the right frequencies are sent to the proper driver for the best quality sound with maximum protection.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Worth every penny and then some. Sounds like I spent a lot of money at the audio store. Bass is as good as most sub woofers. Can't go wrong with these little gems !!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 15, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Installed these in the doors of my vintage '72 Dodge pickup. They replaced the old ones that were shot. The 5" holes (for 6" speakers) which were already there for the old ones fit the new speakers perfectly but I did have to drill new 1/8" holes for mounting the new speakers with their grilles, which was no problem. The speaker wires had blade connectors for the old speakers which went right on the new leads without any modification — so installation couldn't have been easier. I'm very happy with the sound quality. It's just for my AM/FM radio but that's all I want and it sounds excellent and loud and clear over my noisy old truck.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Don't settle for the cheapies!
reviews.reviewText: Absolutely satisfied with these speakers in my o3 wrx! They replaced the stock speakers and sound extraordinarily crisp and clear. They didn't come with speaker wire is the only thing that stood out to me... The back side of the mounting ring has like rubber foam so as to not cause rattling! I got the Kenwood the same size and they sounded terrible and rattled so much my soul is still shaking! If you are getting these for A GD WRX get the front speaker adapter for the love of god! It will save time $ and effort headache and a whole lot of swearing!! You're welcome!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 22, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A lot of punch for a small speaker
reviews.reviewText: I recently restored a Fiat convertible. Being the car is so small I was limited on the size of speaker I could fit. I figured I wouldn't have much bass and that was the trade off of driving a 50 year old convertible. I was also able to run only 25 WPC because of the car's older electrical system. I originally bought the Alpine and no matter how much I EQd them the sound was flat with no bottom end. I then got the RF. I didn't expect that much bottom end from such a small speaker. I would recommend paying a little more to anyone to get these speakers.
